olive oil
2 potato
1 sachet Tex-Mex spice blend
1 tomato
1 bag Slaw Mix
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Plant-Based Aioli
1 packet Mild Chipotle Sauce
½ packet Plant-Based Kumara Patty
2 Plant-Based Burger Buns

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato into wedges, then place on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive
oil, sprinkle over Tex-Mex spice blend, season with salt and toss to coat.
Spread out evenly, then bake until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• SPICY! Chipotle is a mild sauce, but use less if you're sensitive to heat!
• Meanwhile, thinly slice tomato into rounds.
• In a large bowl, combine slaw mix and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and
olive oil. Season to taste and set aside.
• In a small bowl, combine plant-based aioli and 1/2 the mild chipotle sauce.
Season to taste and set aside.

• When the wedges have 10 minutes cook time remaining, heat a large
frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook plant-based kumara patty (see ingredients) until golden, 4-5 minutes
each side.
• Remove pan from the heat, then add remaining chipotle sauce. Turn patties
to coat.
• Meanwhile, bake plant-based burger buns directly on oven rack until
heated through, 3-4 minutes.

• Slice buns in half, then spread with a layer of chipotle aioli. Top with a
chipotle-glazed kumara burger, some tomato and slaw.
• Serve with Tex-Mex wedges and any remaining chipotle aioli.